<div class="comment" id="comment-47776549">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/anovikov">anovikov</a> 5 hours ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">Successful products are usually built from inside the system, not from outside - and then it doesn&#x27;t matter if 50 people from the outside copied it, they won&#x27;t get paid because they aren&#x27;t the right people to begin with.<p>Now problem is, because people from outside usually don&#x27;t know it, and believe they are relevant, they used to create the vast majority of &quot;investment&quot; demand for coding... and now because they ask themselves the same question as you did, they just stopped trying, and their demand is gone.</div>
  
